		<section>
			<title>Constraint Grammar</title>
			<p>Constraint grammar is used in Sahka and Vasta. This is an article based on a presentation held at NODALIDA 2009 CG workshop in Odense.		</p>			<p>
        Antonsen, L., Huhumarniemi, S. and Trosterud, T. 2009: <a href="workshop09_article.pdf">Constraint Grammar in Dialogue Systems</a> </p>

		</section>
		<section>
			<title>The files</title>

<p>Most of the files for OAHPA are in the ped/sme/xml-directory: </p>

<p><strong>Files for the pedagogical lexicon</strong></p>

<ul>
<li>adjectives.xml</li>
<li>fillings.xml (words of other POS) </li>
<li>nouns.xml</li>
<li>numerals.xml</li>
<li>pronouns.xml</li>
<li>propernouns.xml</li>
<li>semantic_sets.xml</li>
<li>verbs.css</li>
<li>verbs.dtd</li>
<li>verbs.xml </li>
</ul>

<p></p>
<p><strong>Files for generating tasks in Morfa-C and Vasta:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>grammar_defaults.xml </li>
<li>questions_adjectives.xml</li>
<li>questions_nouns.xml</li>
<li>questions_numerals.xml</li>
<li>questions_verbs.xml</li>
<li>questions_vasta.xml</li>
</ul>
<p></p>


<p><strong>Files for Sahka:</strong></p> 
<ul>
